SIMPLE: harsh
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harsh
<hw>Harsh</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧rsh)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Harsher</adjf>
<pr>(h⟦aum⟧rsh"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Harshest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>harsk</ets>; akin to G.
<ets>harsch</ets>, Dan. <ets>harsk</ets> rancid, Sw.
<ets>h⟦aum⟧rsk</ets>; from the same source as E. <ets>hard</ets>. See
<er>Hard</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rough;
disagreeable; grating</def>; <specif>esp.:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>disagreeable to the touch.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Harsh</xex>
sand.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Boyle.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>disagreeable to the
taste.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Berries <xex>harsh</xex> and crude.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>disagreeable to the ear.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Harsh</xex> din.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unpleasant and repulsive to the sensibilities;
austere; crabbed; morose; abusive; abusive; severe; rough.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Clarence is so <qex>harsh</qex>, so blunt.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though <qex>harsh</qex> the precept, yet the preacher charmed.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Painting, Drawing, etc.)</fld> <def>Having violent
contrasts of color, or of light and shade; lacking in harmony.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harshly</ent>⟦br⟧
